docs.text: you know you're in for a truly different cinematic experience the moment you realize steve buscemi has been cast as the movie in question's most normal character .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: such is the case with " the big lebowski , " joel and ethan coen's first venture since their " fargo " nabbed nationwide acclaim and a mantlepiece of academy award nods .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there's no need to fear that the coens suffered creative burnout with that accomplishment , because " lebowski " is an effort that makes words like " strange " and " unusual " seem like an understatement .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: thanks in part to delicious characterization and an all-encompassing sense of humor , the film is a smashing success .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the central oddball here is the dude ( jeff bridges ) , an unemployed cad whose ambitions appear to be zilch beyond smoking pot , drinking beer and going bowling ( are you college students already rooting for him , or what ? ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: one night , a pair of thugs break into his house and pee on his carpet , a threatening act that's supposed to be carried out against a famous pasadena millionaire ( david huddleston ) who shares his birth name -- jeff lebowski -- with the dude .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: once the dude realizes this coincidence , he visits the big lebowski in hopes to claim reparations for his soiled rug , and is back to his normal life with alley pals walter ( john goodman ) , a hotheaded vietnam vet , and donny ( buscemi ) , a mild-mannered surfer , before too long .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: soon , though , lebowski's trampy trophy wife bunny ( tara reid ) is kidnaped and held for a hefty ransom , and he turns to the dude for help .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it seems bunny's troubles are related to a line of work she's kept secret from her husband -- she's actually an adult film star and is very in debt with a shady producer named jackie treehorn .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the dude , now on lebowski's payroll , accepts the offer and agrees to handle the money drop ; walter tags along and insists that the dude keep the cash for himself .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: chaos obviously ensues , and the dude eventually finds himself in hot water with cops , crooks and lebowski's ultra-eccentric artist daughter maude ( julianne moore ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: " the big lebowski " deserves to win the coens the same amount of acclaim that " fargo " did ; while that 1996 black comedy was certainly a better film , " lebowski " is at least as breathtakingly imaginative .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the movie boasts a mile-high absurdity level that sometimes threatens to topple over , but thankfully never does .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the coens ( joel directed , ethan produced and both wrote ) keep you in stitches as they unravel their exceedingly loopy tale , and must be commended for juggling a number of people and subplots one would expect to find in a robert altman flick .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: whether we're watching bridges fend off a marmet in his bathtub or moore don viking duds and dance in a busby berkeley-esque dream sequence , " the big lebowski " is immensely lively .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there are those who will dislike this film , but not because it's boring .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the cast has a great deal of fun with the bounteous material they're given .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: bridges exudes a likeable , surprisingly sweet presence ; his dude sure isn't the cleanest guy around , but you'd still follow him to another movie .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: goodman merits 1998's first oscar consideration , as walter's manic temper is one of " the big lebowski " 's many highlights ; the same goes for moore , whose throaty , delectable performance as maude is a hilarious hoot .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: john turturro may very well steal the movie with his two scenes as a colorful bowler from a rival faction .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: sam elliott's rambling narration gets the film off to a solid start .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and some will recognize peter stormare -- " fargo " 's silent heavy -- as carl hungus , a porn star who's really a samurai sword-wielding german nihilist and has-been pop star .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: only in its final third does the movie falter , with a couple of loose plot threads and some cast members who quickly disappear and never emerge for a curtain call .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: these flaws are forgivable , though -- the coens have crafted a tale so rich with personality that it's hard to look at the final product with anything but a big grin on your face .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: without a doubt , " the big lebowski " is the best film so far this year .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: sure , we're only three months in and the competition ( " deep rising , " " desperate measures , " " the wedding singer , " etc . ) has been pretty bland , but it's still the gospel truth .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: maybe during next awards season , " lebowski " won't be a far cry from " fargo . "
docs.label: positive
